WEBVTT

00:00.079 --> 00:02.729
The film on this site's front page cost

00:02.740 --> 00:07.269
$14.20 to produce, start to finish,

00:07.399 --> 00:10.689
all in, and I can document every cent.

00:10.859 --> 00:13.289
Here's the problem with most portfolios,

00:13.439 --> 00:15.409
you have to take their word for it.

00:15.500 --> 00:18.769
A nice reel, big claims, no receipts.

00:18.979 --> 00:20.589
This site works differently.

00:21.319 --> 00:25.189
It runs like a newsroom. Every claim links

00:25.079 --> 00:28.609
to a source. Every illustration says how

00:28.499 --> 00:31.189
it was made and the systems that made them

00:31.079 --> 00:33.029
are public. Take the flagship,

00:33.079 --> 00:36.589
PictureLock. Step one, you hand it a plaintext

00:36.579 --> 00:39.849
script. Step two, it generates the narration,

00:39.859 --> 00:41.810
the score, the sound design,

00:41.820 --> 00:44.669
the shots, the captions, even a Spanish

00:44.619 --> 00:51.499
dub. Step three, it logs every call,

00:51.429 --> 00:54.979
model, and cost to a run manifest and prints

00:54.869 --> 00:58.339
the receipt. That's how a 53-second film

00:58.309 --> 01:01.439
lands at $14.20. And the same gates that

01:01.349 --> 01:03.979
checked it, check this whole site; voice

01:03.890 --> 01:08.259
scoring, code review, resolution audits.

01:08.309 --> 01:11.439
Public, dated, zero open flags.

01:11.859 --> 01:13.969
Even this voice is synthetic,

01:14.039 --> 01:16.469
cloned from me with my consent.

01:17.079 --> 01:21.589
I'm Mitchell. If you're hiring for AI production

01:21.499 --> 01:24.149
work, there's a 12-minute path from start

01:24.039 --> 01:25.829
to verdict. So look around,

01:25.880 --> 01:27.989
check the receipts, and when you're ready,

01:28.139 --> 01:29.009
come find me.
